### 2. PostgreSQL Teenuse Haldamine / Managing PostgreSQL Service / Управление службой PostgreSQL

#### Eesti keel

PostgreSQL töötab süsteemiteenusena (systemd), mida saab hallata käskudega `systemctl`.

| Käsu näide                          | Selgitus                                                               |
| ----------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `sudo systemctl status postgresql`  | Kontrollib teenuse staatust.                                           |
| `sudo systemctl start postgresql`   | Käivitab PostgreSQL teenuse.                                           |
| `sudo systemctl stop postgresql`    | Peatab teenuse.                                                        |
| `sudo systemctl restart postgresql` | Taaskäivitab teenuse, vajalik konfiguratsioonimuudatuste jõustamiseks. |
| `sudo systemctl enable postgresql`  | Lubab teenuse automaatse käivitumise süsteemi alglaadimisel.           |

Näide terminalis:

```bash
sudo systemctl status postgresql
```

Oodatud väljund (osa):

```
● postgresql.service - PostgreSQL RDBMS
   Loaded: loaded (/lib/systemd/system/postgresql.service; enabled; vendor preset: enabled)
   Active: active (running) since ...
```

#### English

PostgreSQL runs as a systemd service which can be managed using `systemctl` commands.

| Command example                     | Explanation                                                  |
| ----------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------ |
| `sudo systemctl status postgresql`  | Checks the status of the service.                            |
| `sudo systemctl start postgresql`   | Starts the PostgreSQL service.                               |
| `sudo systemctl stop postgresql`    | Stops the service.                                           |
| `sudo systemctl restart postgresql` | Restarts the service, necessary for applying config changes. |
| `sudo systemctl enable postgresql`  | Enables automatic start at boot time.                        |

Example:

```bash
sudo systemctl status postgresql
```

Expected output snippet:

```
● postgresql.service - PostgreSQL RDBMS
   Loaded: loaded (/lib/systemd/system/postgresql.service; enabled; vendor preset: enabled)
   Active: active (running) since ...
```

#### Русский

PostgreSQL работает как служба systemd, которой управляют с помощью команд `systemctl`.

| Пример команды                      | Объяснение                                                                |
| ----------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `sudo systemctl status postgresql`  | Проверить статус службы.                                                  |
| `sudo systemctl start postgresql`   | Запустить службу PostgreSQL.                                              |
| `sudo systemctl stop postgresql`    | Остановить службу.                                                        |
| `sudo systemctl restart postgresql` | Перезапустить службу, необходимо для применения изменений в конфигурации. |
| `sudo systemctl enable postgresql`  | Включить автоматический запуск службы при загрузке системы.               |

Пример:

```bash
sudo systemctl status postgresql
```

Ожидаемый вывод (фрагмент):

```
● postgresql.service - PostgreSQL RDBMS
   Loaded: loaded (/lib/systemd/system/postgresql.service; enabled; vendor preset: enabled)
   Active: active (running) since ...
```
